{"word":"πεπαίνω","slug":"πεπαίνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πεπαίνω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πέπων'><el>πέπων</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to ripen, make ripe</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>διασκοπῶν τὰς ἀμπέλους, εἰ πεπαίνουσιν ἤδη</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> if the grapes are ripening, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to become ripe</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to soften, assuage anger</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; of a person, <el>ἢν πεπανθῆις</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}